comments.body:
Hi [~sunilg]

Thanks for the comments. Pls see my response below
{quote} # CsiAdaptorPlugin getAdaptor, we can have isAssignableFrom check to see whether it is a correct impl of not.{quote}
This is already handled in \{{conf.getClass(...)}}

{code}
if (theClass != null && !xface.isAssignableFrom(theClass))
 throw new RuntimeException(theClass+" not "+xface.getName());

{code}
{quote}During serviceStart of CsiAdaptorServices, any exception handling is needed?
{quote}
This is just like a \{{CompositeService}}, if any of sub-service failed to start, then it will throw an exception and cause CsiAdaptorServices failed to started. I don't think we need any extra handling here.
{quote}Could we rename CsiAdaptor4Test to MockCsiAdaptor or something similar.
{quote}
Sure, renamed it to {{MockCsiAdaptor}}.

Updated v4 patch.

Thanks

